.Dd May 16, 2007
.Dt PCIFS 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm pcifs
.Nd refuse-based virtual file system to display devices on PCI bus
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl v
.Op Fl b Ar bus
.Ar mount_point
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility can be used to mount a virtual file system which
under the
mount point, showing the layout
of devices on the PCI bus.
.Pp
The following arguments can be used:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl b Ar bus
Use the numeric bus number from the argument for
the PCI bus number to list.
.It Fl v
Produce verbose output
.El
.Pp
The
.Nm
utility makes use of the
.Xr virtdir 3
virtual directory routines.
.Pp
The
.Xr refuse 3
library is used to provide the file system features.
.Pp
The mandatory parameter is
the local mount
point.
.Pp
The
.Xr pcictl 8
utility is used to retrieve the information on
PCI devices.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr puffs 3 ,
.Xr refuse 3 ,
.Xr virtdir 3 ,
.Xr pcictl 8
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Nm
utility first appeared in
.Nx 5.0 .
